    <div class="card doc-section" id="dod-consent">
      <div class="card-header"><span class="card-header-icon">&#x26A0;&#xFE0F;</span><div><div class="card-title">DoD Consent Banner</div><div class="card-subtitle">System-use notification modal with cookie-based consent tracking</div></div></div>
      <div class="card-body prose">
        <p>A blocking modal overlay that appears on the user's first visit and requires explicit acknowledgment. Consent is stored as a browser cookie (<code>Accepted=Yes</code>) with a 1-day expiry. No server calls are made in v1.0 &mdash; consent is tracked client-side only.</p>
        <p><strong>How it works</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>On <code>DOMContentLoaded</code>, the script checks for the <code>Accepted</code> cookie.</li>
          <li>If absent, the modal fades in after a 1-second delay and the background overlay is displayed.</li>
          <li>Clicking <strong>I Acknowledge</strong> or the &#x2715; close button sets the cookie and fades out the modal.</li>
        </ul>
        <p><strong>Required page markup</strong></p>
        <p>This HTML must be present in the page DOM &mdash; add it to your header Web Template. Do not change the <code>id</code> or <code>class</code> values; the JavaScript references them by exact name.</p>
        <div class="code-block">
&lt;<span class="tag">div</span> <span class="attr">id</span>=<span class="str">"cookieConsent"</span>&gt;
  &lt;<span class="tag">a</span> <span class="attr">id</span>=<span class="str">"closeCookieConsent"</span>&gt;&#x2715;&lt;/<span class="tag">a</span>&gt;
  &lt;<span class="tag">p</span>&gt;Your AO-approved system-use notification text here.&lt;/<span class="tag">p</span>&gt;
  &lt;<span class="tag">a</span> <span class="attr">class</span>=<span class="str">"cookieConsentOK"</span>&gt;I Acknowledge&lt;/<span class="tag">a</span>&gt;
&lt;/<span class="tag">div</span>&gt;
&lt;<span class="tag">div</span> <span class="attr">class</span>=<span class="str">"consentBackground"</span>&gt;&lt;/<span class="tag">div</span>&gt;</div>
        <div class="callout callout-warning"><span class="callout-icon">&#x26A0;&#xFE0F;</span><div>Replace the placeholder text inside <code>&lt;p&gt;</code> with your organization's AO-approved system-use notification language before deploying to production.</div></div>
        <p><strong>Power Pages setup</strong></p>
        <div class="steps" style="margin-top:8px">
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">1</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Create the banner-core.css web file</div><div class="step-desc">Portal Management &rarr; Content &rarr; Web Files &rarr; New. Name: <code>banner-core.css</code>. Partial URL: <code>/banner-core.css</code>. Parent Page: Home. Publishing State: Published. Save, then attach the CSS content from <code>dodbl_bannercore</code> as a Note attachment.</div></div></div>
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">2</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Create the dod-consent-banner.js web file</div><div class="step-desc">Repeat the process. Name: <code>dod-consent-banner.js</code>. Partial URL: <code>/dod-consent-banner.js</code>. Attach the JavaScript content from <code>dodbl_dodconsentbanner</code> (the <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> block contents only, without the tags) as a Note attachment.</div></div></div>
          <div class="step"><div class="step-num">3</div><div class="step-content"><div class="step-title">Add to the header Web Template</div><div class="step-desc">Add the following to your site's header Web Template to enable banners on every page:</div></div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:8px">
&lt;<span class="tag">link</span> <span class="attr">rel</span>=<span class="str">"stylesheet"</span> <span class="attr">href</span>=<span class="str">"/banner-core.css"</span>&gt;
&lt;<span class="tag">script</span> <span class="attr">src</span>=<span class="str">"/dod-consent-banner.js"</span> <span class="attr">defer</span>&gt;&lt;/<span class="tag">script</span>&gt;

<span class="cmt">&lt;!-- Consent modal markup --&gt;</span>
&lt;<span class="tag">div</span> <span class="attr">id</span>=<span class="str">"cookieConsent"</span>&gt;
  &lt;<span class="tag">a</span> <span class="attr">id</span>=<span class="str">"closeCookieConsent"</span>&gt;&#x2715;&lt;/<span class="tag">a</span>&gt;
  &lt;<span class="tag">p</span>&gt;Your AO-approved system-use notification text here.&lt;/<span class="tag">p</span>&gt;
  &lt;<span class="tag">a</span> <span class="attr">class</span>=<span class="str">"cookieConsentOK"</span>&gt;I Acknowledge&lt;/<span class="tag">a</span>&gt;
&lt;/<span class="tag">div</span>&gt;
&lt;<span class="tag">div</span> <span class="attr">class</span>=<span class="str">"consentBackground"</span>&gt;&lt;/<span class="tag">div</span>&gt;</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card doc-section" id="cui-banner">
      <div class="card-header"><span class="card-header-icon">&#x1F3F7;&#xFE0F;</span><div><div class="card-title">CUI Classification Mark</div><div class="card-subtitle">Color-coded classification bar via CSS &mdash; no JavaScript required</div></div></div>
      <div class="card-body prose">
        <p>Renders a full-width color-coded banner above or below any container element using the CSS <code>::before</code> pseudo-element. Text and color are driven entirely by the <code>data-classification</code> attribute.</p>
        <p><strong>Top banner</strong></p>
        <div class="code-block">&lt;<span class="tag">div</span> <span class="attr">class</span>=<span class="str">"classification-banner"</span> <span class="attr">data-classification</span>=<span class="str">"CUI"</span>&gt;
  <span class="cmt">&lt;!-- page content --&gt;</span>
&lt;/<span class="tag">div</span>&gt;</div>
        <p><strong>Bottom banner</strong></p>
        <div class="code-block">&lt;<span class="tag">div</span> <span class="attr">class</span>=<span class="str">"classification-banner-bot"</span> <span class="attr">data-classification</span>=<span class="str">"S"</span>&gt;
  <span class="cmt">&lt;!-- page content --&gt;</span>
&lt;/<span class="tag">div</span>&gt;</div>
        <p><strong>Custom label text</strong> &mdash; use <code>data-banner-content</code> to override the displayed text without changing the color:</p>
        <div class="code-block">&lt;<span class="tag">div</span> <span class="attr">class</span>=<span class="str">"classification-banner"</span>
     <span class="attr">data-classification</span>=<span class="str">"CUI"</span>
     <span class="attr">data-banner-content</span>=<span class="str">"CONTROLLED UNCLASSIFIED INFORMATION"</span>&gt;
&lt;/<span class="tag">div</span>&gt;</div>
        <p><strong>Power Pages setup</strong> &mdash; only the CSS web file is required. Create the <code>banner-core.css</code> web file (Step 1 above), then add one tag to your header Web Template:</p>
        <div class="code-block">&lt;<span class="tag">link</span> <span class="attr">rel</span>=<span class="str">"stylesheet"</span> <span class="attr">href</span>=<span class="str">"/banner-core.css"</span>&gt;</div>
        <div class="callout callout-info"><span class="callout-icon">&#x2139;&#xFE0F;</span><div>Color lookup uses the <strong>first two characters</strong> of <code>data-classification</code>. Values are <strong>case-sensitive</strong>: use <code>CU</code> for CUI purple, <code>U</code> for green, <code>CO</code> for blue, <code>S</code> for red, <code>T</code> for orange. See the <a href="#classification-levels">Classification Levels</a> table for all values.</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card doc-section" id="web-resources">
      <div class="card-header"><span class="card-header-icon">&#x1F4E6;</span><div><div class="card-title">Web Resource Reference</div><div class="card-subtitle">All five web resources included in this solution</div></div></div>
      <div class="card-body" style="padding:0">
        <table class="ref-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Schema Name</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><div class="schema-name">dodbl_bannercore</div><div style="font-weight:600;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px">banner-core</div></td><td><span class="badge badge-info">CSS</span></td><td>Shared stylesheet. Responsive DoD consent modal layout and classification mark color rules for all five levels. Must be loaded before any banner markup.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><div class="schema-name">dodbl_dodconsentbanner</div><div style="font-weight:600;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px">dod-consent-banner</div></td><td><span class="badge badge-info">HTML</span></td><td>Consent modal logic. Vanilla JavaScript for cookie-based consent tracking and fade animation. For Power Pages: extract the <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> block contents into a separate <code>.js</code> web file.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><div class="schema-name">dodbl_cuiconsentbanner</div><div style="font-weight:600;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px">cui-consent-banner</div></td><td><span class="badge badge-info">HTML</span></td><td>CUI classification mark fragment. Single <code>&lt;link&gt;</code> reference to <code>dodbl_bannercore</code>. CSS-only &mdash; no JavaScript required.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><div class="schema-name">dodbl_webtemplatesource</div><div style="font-weight:600;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px">web-template-source</div></td><td><span class="badge badge-info">HTML</span></td><td>Power Pages Web Template source. Open in a browser to copy the Liquid source for the <code>dod-consent-banner</code> Web Template. Supports optional <code>BannerEnabled</code> and <code>DoDConsentText</code> site settings.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><div class="schema-name">dodbl_docs</div><div style="font-weight:600;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px">docs</div></td><td><span class="badge badge-optional">HTML</span></td><td>This documentation page. Link from the Model-Driven App sitemap for in-environment access.</td></tr>
            <tr><td><div class="schema-name">dodbl_release-notes</div><div style="font-weight:600;font-size:12px;margin-top:2px">release-notes</div></td><td><span class="badge badge-optional">HTML</span></td><td>Version history and changelog for all solution releases.</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
